  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-04-01",
    "date": "2021-06-07T23:34:50Z",
    "text": "Meeting IMD Needs with Direction Act or the MIND Act\n\nThis bill temporarily allows states to receive federal Medicaid payment for services provided in institutions for mental diseases (IMDs) during the public health emergency relating to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) and for 180 days after the emergency ends.\n\nCurrent law generally prohibits federal payment under Medicaid for services provided in IMDs for individuals under the age of 65 (although states may receive payment through certain mechanisms, such as through a Medicaid demonstration waiver)."
  },
